# Codex Session Capture Plugin Strategy

## Problem

Codex transcript files exist locally under `~/.codex/sessions/**`, and a Stop hook currently posts transcript deltas to JoelClaw Central. However `joelclaw session search` does not reliably return Codex sessions from this machine. Search falls back to Pi-local transcript roots, so Codex captures are effectively invisible to the session-search workflow.

## Receipts

- Codex hooks config: `/Users/joel/.codex/hooks.json`
  - `Stop` hook runs `JOELCLAW_CENTRAL_URL=http://panda:3000 /opt/homebrew/bin/node /Users/joel/.local/bin/joelclaw-capture-codex-session.js`
- Codex capture script: `/Users/joel/.local/bin/joelclaw-capture-codex-session.js`
  - reads Codex hook stdin: `session_id`, `transcript_path`, `cwd`, `model`, `turn_id`
  - posts delta to `${JOELCLAW_CENTRAL_URL}/api/runs`
  - writes `~/.joelclaw/codex-session-state.json`
  - writes `~/.joelclaw/codex-capture.log`
  - outboxes failed POST bodies to `~/.joelclaw/outbox/`
- Claude config: `/Users/joel/.claude/settings.json`
  - `Stop` hook runs `/Users/joel/.bun/bin/joelclaw-capture-session`
  - configured `JOELCLAW_CENTRAL_URL=http://panda.tail7af24.ts.net:3000`
- Codex plugin examples:
  - plugin manifest path shape: `.codex-plugin/plugin.json`
  - local marketplace config uses `[plugins."name@local-user-plugins"] enabled = true`
  - installed plugin cache lives under `~/.codex/plugins/cache/local-user-plugins/...`

## Current gap

The Stop hook captures deltas to Central/outbox/state, but session discovery/search does not consume Codex local transcript roots or Central captured `agent_runtime=codex` runs. A plugin alone will not fix search unless it also gives Codex/JoelClaw an installable capture + verification surface and/or updates JoelClaw search indexing.

Latest receipt: `node joelclaw-session-capture/scripts/doctor-codex-session-capture.js` passes hook/state/Central checks but fails the search check because `joelclaw session search --source local` returns only Pi paths for the known Codex session id. That is the exact bug to patch in JoelClaw CLI local search.

## Recommended shape

Build a local Codex plugin named `joelclaw-session-capture` with:

1. `.codex-plugin/plugin.json`
   - description tells Codex/Joel to use it for session capture verification and recovery.
   - bundled skill/docs explain the capture lifecycle.
2. `scripts/capture-codex-session.js`
   - promote the current `~/.local/bin/joelclaw-capture-codex-session.js` into versioned source.
   - keep Stop-hook-safe behavior: exit 0, valid JSON, no secrets printed, outbox on failure.
   - use `http://panda.tail7af24.ts.net:3000` instead of ambiguous `http://panda:3000` unless local DNS is guaranteed.
3. `scripts/doctor-codex-session-capture.js`
   - checks hook is installed in `~/.codex/hooks.json`.
   - checks latest transcript path exists.
   - checks state/log mtime.
   - checks outbox count.
   - runs a Central/query/search verification when auth/backplane is available.
4. Installer command/script
   - idempotently patches `~/.codex/hooks.json` Stop hooks.
   - preserves existing cmux hooks.
   - registers/enables `[plugins."joelclaw-session-capture@local-user-plugins"]` in `~/.codex/config.toml` or local marketplace.
5. JoelClaw search fix
   - update `joelclaw session search --source local` to include `~/.codex/sessions/**/*.jsonl`, not just Pi sessions.
   - alternatively add `--agent codex|pi|claude|all` and include Codex roots in raw local search.

## Implementation receipts

Created local plugin scaffold in this repo:

```txt
joelclaw-session-capture/
  .codex-plugin/plugin.json
  README.md
  skills/session-capture/SKILL.md
  scripts/capture-codex-session.js
  scripts/doctor-codex-session-capture.js
  scripts/install-hook.js
```

Changes made:

- Promoted `/Users/joel/.local/bin/joelclaw-capture-codex-session.js` into `joelclaw-session-capture/scripts/capture-codex-session.js`.
- Changed the versioned script default Central URL to `http://panda.tail7af24.ts.net:3000`.
- Ran `JOELCLAW_CENTRAL_URL=http://panda.tail7af24.ts.net:3000 node joelclaw-session-capture/scripts/install-hook.js`, which updated `/Users/joel/.codex/hooks.json` while preserving cmux hooks.
- Doctor check with stable Central URL:
  - hook exists: pass
  - cmux preserved: pass
  - stable panda URL: pass
  - latest Codex transcript exists: pass
  - Codex state/log present: pass, but stale by ~10h because no newer Codex Stop event has fired
  - outbox count: 0
  - Central reachable: pass, `OPTIONS /api/runs` returned 204
  - local JoelClaw search returns Codex path: fail; returned only Pi paths for `019e616b-d7ea-7e33-8004-1e47ac0424b0`

## JoelClaw CLI search fix receipt

Patched on `ssh joel@panda` in `/Users/joel/Code/joelhooks/joelclaw` and pushed to `origin/main`:

- Commit: `8c12b717 fix: search raw Claude and Codex session transcripts`
- Rebased panda `main` onto `origin/main`, then pushed `514be296..8c12b717`.
- Rebuilt and installed `~/.bun/bin/joelclaw` on panda.
- Copied the rebuilt binary from panda to local `~/.bun/bin/joelclaw`, after making a timestamped local backup.

Behavior now:

```bash
joelclaw session search "019e616b-d7ea-7e33-8004-1e47ac0424b0" \
  --source local \
  --machine "$(hostname -s)" \
  --runtime codex \
  --limit 5 \
  --extract
```

Returns:

```txt
/Users/joel/.codex/sessions/2026/05/25/rollout-2026-05-25T16-15-18-019e616b-d7ea-7e33-8004-1e47ac0424b0.jsonl
```

Additional verification:

```bash
joelclaw session extract "019e616b-d7ea-7e33-8004-1e47ac0424b0" --query "pi-notes" --format json
```

Resolved the Codex path and extracted 570 transcript lines.

## Acceptance checks

- Start/stop a Codex session and see a new `captured run=... runtime:codex` line in `~/.joelclaw/codex-capture.log`.
- `~/.joelclaw/codex-session-state.json` advances byte offset for that transcript.
- `joelclaw session search "<unique codex phrase>" --source local --machine "$(hostname -s)" --limit 5 --extract` returns the Codex transcript path, not only Pi sessions that mention it.
- `session_capture_status` reports Codex capture present and fresh.
